<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="360" pageId="14" pageNumber="359" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,865,1752,1774]" box="[151,865,1752,1774]" pageId="14" pageNumber="359">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,1753,1774]" pageId="14" pageNumber="359">Type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Last &amp; White, 2013" authorityName="Last &amp; White" authorityYear="2013" box="[287,687,1752,1774]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="javaensis">
<emphasis box="[287,476,1753,1774]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="359">Dasyatis javaensis</emphasis>
Last &amp; White, 2013
</taxonomicName>
; newly proposed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1818,2023]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1436,151,608]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="360" pageId="14" pageNumber="359">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,278,1818,1843]" pageId="14" pageNumber="359">Definition.</emphasis>
Small dasyatids (adults typically to 
<quantity box="[685,796,1819,1843]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="14" pageNumber="359" unit="cm" value="27.5" valueMax="32.0" valueMin="23.0">23–32 cm</quantity>
DW) characterised by the following: strongly depressed, oval to suboval disc with pectoral-fin apex broadly rounded; snout acutely angular and elongate (1.9–3.6 times combined orbit and spiracle length); eye small and protruding slightly; nasal curtain broadly skirt shaped; mouth medium-sized with 2–4 oral papillae; tail rather short and semi-rigid or filamentous distally (length 1–2.2 times DW), its base broad and strongly or weakly depressed; pelvic fins small to medium-sized, protruding slightly beyond disc; dorsal fold and ventral folds absent (low ridges present in 
<taxonomicName box="[972,1073,1998,2023]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="14" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walga">
<emphasis box="[972,1073,1998,2023]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="359">B. walga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); caudal sting close to tail base (distance from pectoral-fin insertion to caudal-sting base 1.4–2 times interspiracular width); denticle band well developed with edge sharply defined, skin on rest of disc naked; median thorns on disc weak, those on tail larger when present; no scapular thorns and rarely denticles on posterior tail; dorsal coloration plain; ventral surface white, disc margin dark edged; posterior tail plain or with pale lateral stripe; marine, Indo– 
<collectingRegion box="[1166,1223,260,285]" country="Tanzania" name="Mjini Magharibi" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">West</collectingRegion>
Pacific.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="360" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,608]" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,295,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">Species</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bleeker, 1852" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1852" box="[302,622,295,320]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heterura">
<emphasis box="[302,433,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">B. heterura</emphasis>
(Bleeker, 1852)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bloch &amp; Schneider, 1801" authorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" authorityYear="1801" box="[636,1101,295,320]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="imbricata">
<emphasis box="[636,778,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">B. imbricata</emphasis>
(Bloch &amp; Schneider, 1801)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Last &amp; White, 2013" authorityName="Last &amp; White" authorityYear="2013" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="javaensis">
<emphasis box="[1115,1252,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">B. javaensis</emphasis>
(Last &amp; White, 2013)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Muller &amp; Henle, 1841" authorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" authorityYear="1841" box="[277,655,332,357]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walga">
<emphasis box="[277,377,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">B. walga</emphasis>
(Müller &amp; Henle, 1841)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="360" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,608]" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,368,392]" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">Etymology</emphasis>
. Combination of the Latin 
<emphasis box="[644,700,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">brevi</emphasis>
(short) and Greek 
<taxonomicName authority="Cuvier, 1816" authorityName="Cuvier" authorityYear="1816" box="[922,995,369,392]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Trygon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="362" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[922,995,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">trygon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(stingray) reflects the short and semirigid tail of all members of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="360" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,151,608]" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,440,464]" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">Remarks</emphasis>
. Newly erected, morphologically conservative genus with four small species previously placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,274,477,500]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Himantura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">Himantura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The taxonomy of this group is very confused and is the subject of a generic review in progress (PL, unpublished). 
<taxonomicName authority="Bleeker, 1852" authorityName="Bleeker" authorityYear="1852" box="[315,745,511,536]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heterura">
<emphasis box="[315,556,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">Brevitrygon heterura</emphasis>
(Bleeker, 1852)
</taxonomicName>
is the correct name of a common 
<collectingRegion box="[1158,1249,512,535]" country="Solomon Islands" name="Western" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">Western</collectingRegion>
Pacific species, misidentified as 
<taxonomicName box="[341,464,549,572]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Himantura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[341,464,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">Himantura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName box="[499,632,549,572]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="359" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[499,632,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">Brevitrygon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName authority="Muller &amp; Henle, 1841" authorityName="Muller &amp; Henle" authorityYear="1841" box="[651,1008,548,573]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walga">
<emphasis box="[651,720,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">walga</emphasis>
(Müller &amp; Henle, 1841)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[1022,1234,548,573]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walga">
<emphasis box="[1022,1234,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">Brevitrygon walga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bloch &amp; Schneider, 1801" authorityName="Bloch &amp; Schneider" authorityYear="1801" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Brevitrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="360" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="imbricata">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="360">B. imbricata</emphasis>
(Bloch &amp; Schneider, 1801)
</taxonomicName>
are both confined to the Indian Ocean.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
